1. Check for Israeli Background: Determine if the user has specified Israeli Background (e.g., Returning Minor, Katin Chozer, Ezrach Oleh, Toshav Hozer, etc.).
2. If Israeli Background is unknown:
    ◦ Call the &apos;Answer Questions with Ogdan&apos; action with the query &quot;General Documents for Immigration to Israel&quot;
    ◦ Present the list of general documents along with the information for each document (requirements, notes, validity, definitions).
    ◦ Mandatory: Append the exact disclaimer: &apos;You may be asked to provide additional documents based on your specific aliya status and Israeli background&apos;. Ask the user &quot;Would you like more information on special Aliyah statuses and Israeli background?&quot;.
3. If Israeli Background is Known (or Selected):
    ◦ Call the &apos;Answer Questions with Ogdan&apos; action using the specific Israeli Background as a search query (e.g., &apos;documents for Katin Chozer&apos;).
    ◦ Present the specific document list retrieved for that status.</description>
